50|$|Beant Singh {{became the}} chief {{minister}} of Punjab in 1992. Beant Singh's tenure as the <b>chief</b> minister <b>witnessed</b> the Punjab insurgency. Under him, the Punjab Police crushed the pro-Khalistan militants forcefully, inviting claims {{of human rights}} violations.|$|R
50|$|Her tenth book, Evil Relations (2012), was {{nominated}} for the CWA Gold Dagger Award for Non-Fiction. Written in conjunction with David Smith, <b>chief</b> prosecution <b>witness</b> in the Moors Murders case it details, for the first time, Smith's story in full.|$|R
